24 Nov 2017 15:02






The legend of Loreley. A mermaid or the like living on or in a rock in the river Rhein. There is a quite famous poem by Heinrich Heine, naming the mermaid and describing her melancholy-inducing song. The area has been a hotspot for ship accidents for centuries: The river currents are treacherous enough, and once when the river had very little water I could see lots of small, sharp rocks just peeping out of the water; as the water is usually quite mirky they are invisible at normal water levels. So there is plenty of normal potential for accidents there. In addition, the area is (rightfully) renowned for being the most beautiful part of the river valley. This combination led to widespread belief (or rather a very popular legend) of that mermaid's song causing these accidents. Except that I am unaware of anything whaly involved in that - the maid is just described as a blond and beautiful mermaid.







